01266 /**
01267  * cvmx_denc#_tc_static_epdcch_reg#
01268  *
01269  * These registers store the EREG pattern table used for E-PDCCH symbol
01270  * mapping. The default values of these registers are configured for normal
01271  * usage in accordance with the 3GPP specifications release 11, and there
01272  * should be no reason to change the default values in these registers.
01273  *
01274  * There are 5 EREG patterns corresponding to different CP modes. Each
01275  * pattern consists of 840 bits, and the 5 patterns are concatenated to form
01276  * a single vector of 4200 bits, stored in 66 x 64-bit registers.
01277  *
01278  * The combined pattern vector can be indexed as follows:
01279  *
01280  * _ vector[(840*i + 60*t + 5*(s+1) - 1):(840*i + 60*t + 5*s)] = P(i,t,s)
01281  *
01282  * Where i is the CP mode index [0,4], t is the OFDM symbol [0,13], and s is
01283  * the sub-carrier within the RB [0,11].
01284  *
01285  * The 5-bit pattern value selects between one of the 16 EREGS when set to a
01286  * value in the range [0,15], and values > 15 indicate that no EREG is mapped
01287  * to that RE.
01288  *
01289  * At reset, the E-PDCCH EREG pattern table is loaded with the appropriate
01290  * patterns for 5 CP modes:
01291  * * 0x0 = Normal CP.
01292  * * 0x1 = Special sub-frame 3, 4, 8, 9 with normal CP.
